## 1) What the project is
Ward Academy тАФ an English-learning platform for children **9тАУ13**, one-on-one live sessions with a teacher, assisted by AI **with the teacher approving every output before it reaches the child**. One curriculum: **"Ward Curriculum"** тАФ a platform-specific curriculum measured against **CEFR (A1тЖТB1)** тАФ 30 units ┬╖ 215 objectives, complete and frozen in `Ward_Curriculum_Master_Reference.md`. (The "school curriculum" track was retired permanently on 2026-06-20.)

## 2) Current status
**The marketing front-end is visually built, and the backend + the four workspaces (Admin/Teacher/Student/Guardian) are built, working, and tested under real isolation, and deployed live on ward.academy (Vercel/fra1). The Admin account is complete, and the **Teacher account (the teaching workspace) is fully built**: a seven-tab student page, a deterministic catalog plan aggregated from "Ward Curriculum" at the confirmed entry level тАФ displayed (PlanView, read-only) and approved тАФ not authored, recurring sessions with internal video (Daily) and reports built on a simple template shared over WhatsApp, manual/digital homework, unit tests generated from the objectives that the student takes and that are auto-graded, and a "Today's Command Center" dashboard. The Student and Guardian accounts mirror this (test results + full reports + the plan with its units).**

- тЬЕ **Design system** (Claude Design): complete and coherent.
- тЬЕ **Landing page**: deployed on ward.academy, **English/LTR by default + an "╪╣" toggle (bilingual, flips to RTL)**, ages 9тАУ13. Rebuilt to be **product-led (show, don't tell)** with the sections: hero (a flower blooming on reveal + a glimpse of the Bloom report) ┬╖ how we work ┬╖ a look inside (guardian app + student simulation) ┬╖ Bloom report (the flower = a skills map) ┬╖ the private teacher (one-on-one session) ┬╖ AI support (teacher-dashboard simulation: "nothing reaches the student before your approval") ┬╖ results (sample numbers) ┬╖ pricing (3 tiers, shared features) ┬╖ parent testimonials ┬╖ FAQ ┬╖ final call. With: gradual reveal on scroll, a sticky booking button on mobile, an extended hero background, green booking buttons, and an OG image.
- тЬЕ **The real enrollment path (bilingual, cookie-driven + toggle):** `/enroll` (register тЖР book тЖР creates a lead, captures the parent's language) ┬╖ `/book/[token]` (booking via a sent link) ┬╖ `/t/[token]` (placement test тАФ the parent opens, the child answers, questions from the DB) ┬╖ `/set-password` (invite-link landing). (`/login`┬╖`/signup`┬╖`/placement` are now **redirects** to their real paths.)
- тЬЕ **Identity & language**: purple is the hero, the flower is identity / the spark is AI, fonts tuned, **Western numerals**, **no emoji**, **no full names** (first names only in the simulation), the AI's messaging is **softened for parents** (the details are for the teacher).
- ЁЯЧСя╕П **Removed**: the `/teacher` and `/brand` pages (the teacher dashboard was built for real in `/studio`).
- тЬЕ **The backend тАФ built and tested (63 migrations on Supabase/Frankfurt, RLS on every table):**
  - **Isolation & identity:** `tenants` (the isolation unit) ┬╖ `profiles` (identity + layered roles) ┬╖ a JWT hook injects `tenant_id`+`roles` (enabled). No role escalation (no client write to `profiles`).
  - **Guardians & students:** `guardianships` (oneтЖТmany + consent per child) ┬╖ profile visibility scoped by role (a guardian sees only their children, a teacher sees their tenant).
  - **Content engine:** the plan is aggregated deterministically from the "Ward Curriculum" catalog (`curriculum_objectives`) at the confirmed entry level ┬╖ `items` (tagged with the catalog objective id) + **a teacher approval gate** ┬╖ `item_keys` (the answer hidden) ┬╖ `assignments`.
  - **Submissions & progress:** `submissions` (trusted server-side grading, no spoofing) ┬╖ `objective_assessments`тЖТ`objective_progress` (the 65/35 decaying average via a trigger) ┬╖ completion is separate from performance.
  - **Sessions:** `sessions` (UTC + DB-level conflict prevention) ┬╖ `session_reports` (AI draft тЖТ edit тЖТ approve тЖТ shown to the family).
  - **One generation service** (`lib/generation/service.ts`, Claude) for original items and report drafts.
- тЬЕ **Workspaces (Next.js, protected by a proxy):** `/studio` (teacher: generate/approve/assign/schedule/reports + student progress + **"My availability"**: she sets her own slots) ┬╖ `/learn` (student) ┬╖ `/guardian` (guardian) ┬╖ `/signup` ┬╖ role-directed sign-in.
- тЬЕ **Admin/Operations account `/admin` тАФ complete and separated from the teacher** (a separate `admin` role, `assertAdmin()` at the head of every service action, a mobile-first `AdminShell` shell). It runs the entire funnel:
  - **Registration** (`/admin/registrations`): a three-stage registration form (studentтЖТguardianтЖТbooking) тЖТ list+detail with a **stage bar** (registration/booking/test/session/payment/accounts) тЖТ booking/rescheduling тЖТ AI placement test тЖТ **AI intro-session report** (draftтЖТreviewтЖТsent to the family via Resend) тЖТ creation of guardian/student accounts (**an invite link**, not a password) + teacher assignment. With editing of contact details, delete/archive, an operations note, and an activity log.
