- тЬЕ **Internal video:** Daily.co (`lib/video.ts` + `VideoCall`): a private room per session, a join token owned by the teacher, role-based authorization.
- тЬЕ **Demo seed (no AI/tokens):** `scripts/seed-demo-class.mjs` builds a class of 5 students with varied personas and months of hand-written history (plans/progress/sessions/reports/homework/tests) to preview the features.
- тЬЕ **Tools + seed:** `npm run db:migrate` / `db:status` / `db:seed`. Test accounts: `admin@ward.local` (Admin) ┬╖ `teacher@ward.local` ┬╖ `student@ward.local` ┬╖ `parent@ward.local`. **Demo teacher account:** `ward@ward.academy` (╪║┘Ж┘И╪й ┘И╪▒╪п / Ghinwa Ward) тАФ demo data (Ghinwa + her students are the seeded demo class, not live operation).

## 3) Pinned decisions (not reopened without cause)
- Identity is **guardian-anchored** (one account per guardian, multiple children, consent required per account).
- **The teacher approves every AI output** before it reaches the child (the core trust model).
- **Progress (the new model):** objective-level assessment with four states (seed/bud/balloon/bloom) decided by the teacher ┬╖ a **65/35 decaying average** at the objective level ┬╖ a simple automatic roll-up for the unit (**the unit flower**) and the major flower (skills across started units). Scope A1тЖТB1 on "Ward Curriculum". **Source of truth: `Ward_Curriculum_Master_Reference.md`.** *(The new model is fully adopted тАФ teacher + auto via the catalog; the old model is retired. The migration completed 2026-06-24.)*
- **Europe data + RLS isolation** between students.
- **Original generation** of content (no ingestion of copyrighted books).
- **Ages 9тАУ13**, **English-first** across the platform: the internal surfaces (child/teacher/admin) are English; the parent surfaces are bilingual with an "╪╣" toggle; and communication is in the parent's saved language (see the language policy below).
- **In the parent-facing UI:** the AI is "a support for the teacher and student", no more; its technical details stay in the teacher UI. Western numerals, no emoji, first names only.
- **Strict separation of responsibilities:** Admin (`/admin`) owns the pre-learning funnel + billing + cases + teacher oversight; the teacher (`/studio`) is for teaching and setting her own availability only; the roles do not overlap.
- **The teacher owns her availability:** she sets/edits it from her account, and Admin views her schedule read-only.
- **Mobile-first across the entire build journey:** every screen is designed and verified on mobile first (the shells use a bottom bar on phones).
- **Language policy (English-first ┬╖ i18n ┬╖ decision 2026-06-24):** all surfaces are English/LTR by default (the child surface is pure, no toggle); Arabic is an optional layer for the parent surfaces (landing ┬╖ enrollment ┬╖ guardian dashboard ┬╖ reports/communication) via a toggle + one-click translation for reports. **i18n from day one** (`en.json` first ┬╖ `ar.json` drop-in). (Details: `Foundation ┬з13`.) **тЬЕ i18n fully complete (2026-06-25):** all surfaces (1тАУ7) converted to `next-intl`, the old system retired and deleted, one system (next-intl + the `LOCALE` cookie) тАФ see "Technical facts ┬зLanguage" and the banner below.
- **Semantic colors, not purple only:** purple is the hero, but use green (success/completion), apricot (a warm invitation / next step), and rose (gentle errors/deletion, limited, no harsh red).
- **Design workflow (pinned decision):** Claude Design is for reusable visual identity only (logo ┬╖ colors ┬╖ font ┬╖ icons ┬╖ the flower/spark) тАФ **no screens**. Screens and pages are built in Claude Code directly. **The deployed code is the source of truth for screens and identity once applied;** code edits are not fed back to Design (Design is a generation tool, not an archive). The new flower (four petals + a seed) and the new logo from Design = the adopted identity that the code must catch up to.
> Full details in: `Ward_Academy_Foundation.md` and `Ward_Academy_Design_System_Brief.md`.

