## 6) How we work (the sync ritual)
- **One source of truth per domain:** curriculum тЖТ Curriculum Reference ┬╖ constitution тЖТ Foundation ┬╖ design тЖТ Design Brief ┬╖ pulse/status тЖТ this file. Truth is not duplicated across two files.
- **Start of any session** (Code/Design): "read `START_HERE.md` first before you begin".
- **End of any Code session**: "update `START_HERE.md`: status + session log + any new decision".
- **A decision is not adopted until it is written in its domain's source of truth**, then referenced here. The direction: decision тЖТ domain document тЖТ pulse here (not the reverse silently).
- **When returning to Claude (Chat)**: share the latest version of this file.
- **(Methodological lesson тАФ a migration ships with its code):** `db:migrate` hits the production database immediately; so any gate carrying a migration is **pushed and deployed in the same round** тАФ no local unpushed commits left behind, otherwise a "database ahead of deployed code" window opens that breaks production. (Happened 2026-06-25 with 0062/0063.)
- **(Methodological lesson тАФ every deploy ends with a live human check):** "green build" proves compilation, not live behavior; **the final verification is by eye on the deployed site**, not by a report alone.
- **(Methodological lesson тАФ "build green" hides whole classes of faults ┬╖ confirmed 2026-06-27):** translation faults (raw i18n keys), font faults, and display/layout issues **do not break the build** тАФ they surface only at runtime. Every affected surface needs a **live visual check** + confirming **Vercel Ready = HEAD**, not just a green compile.
- **(Methodological lesson тАФ font bugs need both-direction visual checks):** verify *both* "Arabic not broken" *and* "English now correct". Rule-level / CSS-resolution proof can pass while the visual still fails тАФ the `Nunito Fallback` (local Arial) Arabic interception was invisible to rule-level analysis and only showed by eye (2026-06-27).
- **(Methodological lesson тАФ delete a file together with its consumer in the SAME commit):** a failed `git add` on a deleted-file pathspec silently splits the change and ships a broken build (missing-module). Use `git add -A` (or `git rm`) and check `git status` before committing.
- **(Methodological lesson тАФ read deploy health from the TOP of the Deployments list):** the newest deployment is live; judging health from a stale failed deployment opened by name gives a false negative (2026-06-27).

## 7) Explicitly out of scope (anti-scope-creep тАФ consult `scope-guardian`)
- No native mobile apps (web only in v1).
- No live payments/subscriptions (pricing is display only for now).
- No in-platform chat/instant messaging in v1.
- No AI generation reaching the child **without** the teacher approval gate.
- No collection of children's data beyond what's needed; consent is always required.

## 8) Pinned technical facts
- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 + Turbopack.
- **Node 20 mandatory** (Node 24 is incompatible with the edge-runtime in Next 16) тАФ pinned in `.nvmrc`.
- **Deployment:** Vercel on `ward.academy`. **Repo:** github.com/diyaaldinhafez/wardacademy, branch `main`.
- **Deployment status (updated on every code push):** the live build on Vercel = code `b7c39dc` (guardian avatar-switcher first-name label тАФ the last app change of the 2026-06-27 session) ┬╖ `HEAD` in sync with `origin/main` ┬╖ production migrations **0055тЖТ0064** (no gap; `0064` = `profiles.comms_locale`) ┬╖ **no mismatch window between the production database and the deployed code.** *(2026-06-27 app commits, in order: `af88b38` i18n `requestLocale` fix ┬╖ `44c3a3c` forced-en `dir=ltr` ┬╖ `4e90acb`/`984768c`/`1392513`/`3c601c3` guardian flower motivation + skill bars ┬╖ `f488f69` session-card trim ┬╖ `b8685ad` global Arabic-font stack ┬╖ `4096559` guardian Arabic-font scoped fix ┬╖ `b7c39dc` switcher label.)*
- **Language (i18n тАФ complete):** `next-intl` v4 only тАФ the language is in the `LOCALE` cookie (default `en`, no path prefixes) via `i18n/request.ts`. **`getRequestConfig` honors `requestLocale` (an explicit `getTranslations({locale})` wins) тЖТ else the `LOCALE` cookie тЖТ else default** (fix `af88b38`, 2026-06-27 тАФ see the dedicated section). The internal surfaces (child/teacher/admin/video) are **forced English** (provider `locale="en"` + `getTranslations({locale:"en"})`) **and pin `dir=ltr`/`lang=en`** so an `ar` cookie cannot right-align them (`44c3a3c`); the parent surfaces (landing/enrollment/test/booking/guardian/set-password) are **bilingual, cookie-driven** + an "╪╣" toggle with dynamic `dir`/`lang`. `messages/{en,ar}.json` (key parity checked programmatically; the forced surfaces are en-only by design). **The old system (`LanguageProvider`/`useT`/`LangToggle`/`lib/i18n`/`lib/content`) is retired and fully deleted.** **Communication + family report content** reach the parent in their saved language (priority: a manual `LOCALE` cookie тЖР `profiles.comms_locale` тЖР `leads.guardian_locale` тЖР `ar`) via `lib/parentLocale.guardianEffectiveLocale` + `getTranslations({locale: parentLocale})` (overriding the operator UI's forced locale).
- **Fonts (identity тАФ fixed 2026-06-27):** `next/font` loads Nunito (Latin body) ┬╖ Baloo 2 (Latin display) ┬╖ IBM Plex Sans Arabic (`--font-ar`, Arabic) тАФ always, all locales. **Arabic glyphs always resolve to IBM Plex Sans Arabic regardless of root `html lang`:** the global `--font-sans` is `var(--font-nunito), var(--font-ar)` (`b8685ad`), and `/guardian` (English UI + Arabic content) pins a scoped per-glyph stack `"Nunito", var(--font-ar), тАж` on its layout wrapper to bypass next/font's `Nunito Fallback` (= local Arial, no `unicode-range`) that was intercepting Arabic glyphs (`4096559`). `html[lang="ar"]` keeps the Arabic face primary on Arabic surfaces (unchanged). See the dedicated section.
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL, EU/Frankfurt) + RLS. **64 migrations** (`supabase/migrations/*.sql`) applied via `npm run db:migrate` (a pg script, the Session pooler string in `.env.local` as `SUPABASE_DB_URL`). The latest is **0064** (`profiles.comms_locale text check (in 'en','ar')` тАФ the saved parent communication language). Before it **0060тАУ0063** (plan unification on the catalog: confirmed level 0060 ┬╖ `items.objective_id`тЖТcatalog 0061 ┬╖ `submissions.objective_id` nullable+trigger decoupled 0062 ┬╖ drop the `objectives` table 0063), and 0055тАУ0059 (catalog/assessment model/old-model retirement/parent language).
- **Role guards (server):** `lib/auth.ts` тЖТ `assertAdmin()` / `assertInstructor()` at the head of every action that uses the service role (RLS alone is not enough since the service key bypasses it). The service-role client is in `lib/supabase/admin.ts`.
- **Email:** Resend (`lib/email.ts`, the `ward.academy` domain DKIM/SPF-verified) тАФ booking confirmation + invite link + intro-session report; it degrades harmlessly if the key is absent. **Dates/time zones:** `luxon` + `tenants.timezone`.
- **Supabase clients:** `lib/supabase/{client,server,admin}.ts` + `proxy.ts`/`lib/supabase/session.ts` (session refresh and protection of `/studio` `/learn` `/guardian`).
- **AI:** `lib/generation/service.ts` (server-only) via `@anthropic-ai/sdk` (model `claude-sonnet-4-6`): items/questions, a session report from the teacher's inputs, a unit test from the objectives, internal diagnostics. The Anthropic spend cap is set ($5 trial).
- **Verification:** `npm run build` before any push. `.env.local` is outside Git (Supabase + Anthropic + DB URL).

## тЬЕ Assessment-model migration тАФ closed and complete (2026-06-24)
> **The deviation item is closed.** The assessment-and-progress model migration completed fully per `Ward_Migration_Plan.md` тАФ five phases, five green gates:
> - **The catalog** (0055): `curriculum_units`/`curriculum_objectives` тАФ "Ward Curriculum" 30/215 (A1тЖТB1), a shared frozen catalog.
> - **The assessment model** (0056): `objective_assessments` (a cumulative log) + `objective_progress` (state) + a **65/35 decaying average** via a trigger, and four `ward_stage_for_value` states (0/4/7/10).
> - **The roll-up** (`lib/progress/bloom.ts`): the unit flower = the average of all its objectives (un-assessed=0) ┬╖ the skill petal = the average across **started units only**. **One** function consumed by the student/guardian/teacher (consistency by construction).
> - **Evidence source:** the teacher decides the state for each objective (teacher/mixed); and **auto** = a unit test linked via `curriculum_unit_id` (0057) тЖТ per-skill ratio тЖТ the ratio key тЖТ `objective_assessments(auto)`.
> - **A B1 cap** across all code/schema ┬╖ **the old bridge was deleted** entirely ┬╖ **the old half is retired** (0058): `progress_records` + the 0007 trigger + the demo/Grade6/null `objectives` rows. (Backup: `backups/phase5_old_model_2026-06-24.json`; `study_plans` and the `objectives` table schema are intact тАФ the builder regenerates.)
>
> **Source of truth for the model:** `Ward_Curriculum_Master_Reference.md`. **Known follow-ups (not a deviation):** per-skill auto accuracy (objective-level accuracy is a future item) ┬╖ a curriculum picker for the teacher to start the objectives of an un-started unit ┬╖ `descriptor_en` for English. (The vocabulary track is deferred out of the MVP тАФ see ┬з9.)

## тЬЕ Assessment model тАФ verdict (2026-06-27): the 3-layer model is CORRECT and FROZEN
> A **planning** session (no code) diagnosed the `/studio` objective-rating flow and reconciled it against the **frozen** `Ward_Curriculum_Master_Reference.md` (┬з1тАУ┬з5). **Verdict: the model is correct and stays frozen тАФ the only issues are a DISPLAY bug + missing history UI + one open Layer-3 question.** (`Ward_Curriculum_Master_Reference.md` was NOT modified тАФ it was confirmed correct.)
> - **Layer 1 (objective):** the **65/35 decaying average over the objective's repeated assessments is CORRECT and intentional** тАФ an objective is assessed **multiple times** across lessons (teacher + auto-graded homework + unit test), so the decay absorbs fluctuation and allows full recovery. **Do NOT change to last-write/replace.** *(This overturns the earlier instinct to "replace at L1"; the per-objective diagnostic's "accumulation" is the model working тАФ the real fault is the display, see below.)*
> - **Layer 2 (unit / "unit flower"):** simple average of **ALL** the unit's objective values (skills mixed) тАФ per reference ┬з5. (Currently implemented as such; no per-unit, per-skill value exists, which is fine for the unit flower.)
> - **Layer 3 (skill petal, across started units):** reference ┬з1/┬з5 says "mean of that skill's objectives across started units" but does **NOT** specify simple-vs-decaying. **OPEN QUESTION (resolve at design time):** should the cross-unit skill petal be a **simple mean** (current code) or a **decaying average across units**? (Diya leans toward decaying across units; not yet decided.)
> - **Confirmed real bug (DISPLAY, not math) тАФ fix during the Plan-section redesign, NOT now:** after Save, the objective `<select>` shows the **bucketed stage of the blended `current_value`** instead of the teacher's just-picked state, so it looks unsaved and lures the teacher into repeated saves (each a genuine new assessment тЖТ the value climbs). The model is fine; the control must instead reflect what was saved / confirm it was recorded. *(Full diagnostic in the session log; tracked as ┬з9 item (12c).)*
> - **New requirement (reference ┬з4/┬з10, just not surfaced):** per-objective **assessment history** for the teacher тАФ count + log (timestamp + SOURCE: teacher / auto-graded homework / unit test), **editable/deletable** with `current_value` recomputed from the remaining rows. The data already exists in `objective_assessments` (each row carries its source); only the UI is missing. *(Tracked as ┬з9 item (12d).)*
> - **Deferred bundle** (design-first, then implement): ┬з9 item **(12)** тАФ objective indicators, the rating dropdown, the display bug, the history UI, and the L3 question.

## тЬЕ Internationalization (i18n) тАФ fully complete (2026-06-25)
> **Only one system: `next-intl` + the `LOCALE` cookie.** Seven surfaces with green gates, and the old system retired and deleted.
> - **The internal surfaces (forced English):** 1 the child `/learn` ┬╖ 2 the teacher `/studio` ┬╖ 3 Admin `/admin` ┬╖ 7b the video. (Provider `locale="en"` + `getTranslations({locale:"en"})`; `messages` are en-only by design.)
> - **The parent surfaces (bilingual, cookie-driven + an "╪╣" toggle + dynamic `dir`):** 4 the guardian ┬╖ 5 landing/enrollment/test/booking ┬╖ 7a `set-password`. (`landing`┬╖`enrollForm`┬╖`placement`┬╖`guardian`┬╖`setPassword`┬╖`common` with checked en/ar key parity.)
> - **Communication (6) in the parent's language:** a single column `leads.guardian_locale` (migration 0059, captured in `/enroll` from the cookie, `ar` fallback). Email (`lib/email`) and WhatsApp (studio/admin) and the `ProvisionPanel` invite are built via `getTranslations({locale: parentLocale})` тАФ **overriding the operator UI's forced locale**. namespace `comms`.
> - **Retirement (connect-before-cut):** `LanguageProvider`┬╖`LangToggle`┬╖`lib/i18n`┬╖`lib/content` + the dead `_AR` maps were deleted, after proving zero importers for each.
> - **The boundary (not translated тАФ data/authored content):** test questions ┬╖ `title_ar` for units ┬╖ plan descriptions ┬╖ teacher/AI report text ┬╖ option labels (the "╪╣" side for `enrollOptions`, live).
> - **~~Deferred by product decision~~ RESOLVED (2026-06-27):** the **AI-generated reports** now follow the parent's language тАФ `generateSessionReportDraft` takes a `locale` and `REPORT_SYSTEM` has `ar`/`en` variants. See "тЬЕ Parent language" (2026-06-27).

## тЬЕ Plan unification on the catalog тАФ complete and closed (2026-06-25)
> The plan is aggregated deterministically from "Ward Curriculum" (`curriculum_objectives`) тАФ no AI generation, no manual authoring. Five green gates:
> - **G1** (9783b18): `confirmed_level` structured and separate from `suggested_level` + a confirm/override control in the funnel (`registrations/[id]`) ┬╖ `confirmed ?? suggested` precedence in five readers ┬╖ migration 0060.
> - **G2** (188187c): the deterministic aggregator `aggregatePlanItems(level)` (`lib/curriculum/aggregatePlan.ts`) тАФ `order by unit_number, seq, objective_id`, fills `items` in the existing shape (`id=objective_id` ┬╖ `unit=title_ar` ┬╖ `description=descriptor_ar` ┬╖ `level=o.level`). A decisive decision: `level=o.level` (the nominal level), not `cefr_level` тАФ the Stretch+Spiral policy deliberately raises `cefr_level` so it must not be displayed. The `startPlanFromCatalog` path.
> - **G3** (52a6654): re-point the old `objectives` readers тЖТ the catalog ┬╖ migration 0061 (`items.objective_id` тЖТ `curriculum_objectives(objective_id)`, FK on PK) ┬╖ retire `approvePlan`'s write to the old table.
> - **G4** (fcc72d9): remove every non-catalog plan path (`generatePlan`┬╖`generatePlanFromIndex`┬╖the from-index UI┬╖`createManualPlan`┬╖`planTool`) ┬╖ `PlanBuilder`тЖТ`PlanView` a read-only viewer ┬╖ the sole source `startPlanFromCatalog`.
> - **G5** (90f22e8 + seed + 0063): 5a connect G3's leftovers (`/learn` join) ┬╖ 5b rewrite the seed catalog-only (a shared mirror proven byte-for-byte via tsx + progress seeded via `objective_assessments`/the trigger, no injection) + migration 0062 (`submissions.objective_id` nullable + trigger decoupled) ┬╖ 5c migration 0063 (drop the `submissions.objective_id` column + the `objectives` table) + remove the `clearLearnerPlans` no-op + archive gate3/gate5.
>
> **The three governing decisions:** (1) the `items` JSON storage stays, filled from the catalog (zero display breakage) ┬╖ (2) the granularity = one full CEFR level from unit 1 ┬╖ (3) level confirmation in `admin` (the funnel), consistent with the strict separation. The teacher's lever = confirm/override the entry level + the displayтЖТapprove gate, not authoring. **Deliberately deferred:** teacher selection/ordering of objectives. The demo now matches production (same path/shape/catalog ids).

## тЬЕ Account-creation separation тАФ `Add a child` closed (2026-06-27)
> **Architectural deviation closed** (was open item ┬з9(7)). The `Add a child` path inside `/guardian` let a guardian create a learner directly тАФ with **no placement test / level / plan / teacher / consent** тАФ bypassing the strict separation (Foundation ┬з4/┬з7: Admin owns account creation via the funnel тЖТ `provisionAccounts`/invite). It was a **dead remnant of a pre-Admin-funnel model**, so it was **deleted** (not re-engineered). **Registration is now exclusively Admin тЖТ `provisionAccounts`.** Also removed: `grantConsent` + the consent badge/button from `/guardian` (orphaned by the closure тАФ consent is captured at registration, not by the parent later).

## тЬЕ Parent language тАФ everything reaching parents follows the saved parent language (2026-06-27)
> **Decision:** every communication and family-facing content reaches the parent in their **saved language**, not the implicit UI language.
> - **Explicit question** "preferred communication language" added to `/enroll` (step 2) тЖТ `leads.guardian_locale` (replacing implicit derivation from the UI language).
> - **`profiles.comms_locale`** (migration **0064**) тАФ carried at provisioning from the lead + a **manual correction** in `admin/registrations/[id]` (`updateGuardianLocale`).
> - **`/guardian` opens in the parent language** тАФ `lib/parentLocale.guardianEffectiveLocale` (priority: a manual `LOCALE` cookie тЖР `comms_locale` тЖР `ar`).
> - **AI reports generated in the parent language** тАФ `generateSessionReportDraft` takes a `locale`; `REPORT_SYSTEM` has `ar`/`en` variants. *(This resolves the former open item "generated-report language".)*
> - **The five language-mixing spots resolved** тАФ reports drafted in the parent's language + FSI/PDI bidi isolation on injected names + `dir="auto"` on data nodes (no more `"<Arabic name>'s flower spansтАж"` concatenation).
> - **Locked:** `/learn` stays **English-labelled** (constitutional ┬з3); only family **report content** follows the parent language.

## тЬЕ Critical language-system fix + forced-en direction (2026-06-27)
> **Was silently threatening every operational surface.** `getRequestConfig` ignored `requestLocale` and always read the `LOCALE` cookie, so the English-forced surfaces (studio/admin/learn/video) rendered **raw i18n keys** whenever the cookie was `ar` (e.g. the parent switcher set it) тАФ because `ar.json` has no studio/admin/learn/video namespaces.
> - **Fix `af88b38`:** `getRequestConfig(async ({ requestLocale }))` тЖТ an explicit requested locale **overrides** the cookie тЖТ else cookie тЖТ else default. The forced surfaces already pass `getTranslations({locale:"en"})`, so they are now truly forced.
> - **Completion `44c3a3c`:** the forced-en surfaces also pin `dir=ltr`/`lang=en` (studio + admin layout wrappers) so an `ar` cookie can no longer right-align the English UI. (The text was fixed by `af88b38`; the direction leaked from the root `<html dir>`.)
> - **Lesson:** this is the canonical "build green тЙа correct" тАФ raw keys never broke the build; only a live visual with the cookie stuck to `ar` exposed it.

## тЬЕ Arabic-font fix тАФ platform-wide identity bug (2026-06-27)
> **Arabic text rendered in a system/Arial fallback (not the Ward Arabic face) on English-root surfaces.** Two-part root cause: (1) the Arabic face was *applied* only via `html[lang="ar"]`; (2) even after globally adding it, next/font's **`Nunito Fallback` (= `local(Arial)`, no `unicode-range`)** intercepted Arabic glyphs before IBM Plex Sans Arabic.
> - **Global stack `b8685ad`:** `--font-sans: var(--font-nunito), var(--font-ar)` тАФ fixed studio/admin/landing (per-glyph: LatinтЖТNunito, ArabicтЖТPlex). Arabic surfaces unchanged (the `html[lang="ar"]` override is untouched).
> - **`/guardian` scoped `4096559`:** guardian Arabic is plain body text on `--font-sans`, where the Arial fallback still won. Its layout wrapper now pins `"Nunito", var(--font-ar), тАж` (the literal real "Nunito" face, whose `unicode-range` excludes Arabic, then straight to the Arabic face тАФ skipping Arial), only when `locale != ar`. **Arabic now renders in IBM Plex Sans Arabic everywhere; Latin unchanged.**
> - **Lesson:** rule-level/CSS-resolution proof passed while the visual still failed тАФ the Arial interception was invisible to static analysis; both-direction visual checks were required.

## тЬЕ `/guardian` redesign тАФ complete (2026-06-27)
> Replaces the old stacked text-wall.
> - **Structure:** an **avatar child-switcher** (`?child=`, first-name label, no mid-word truncation) + a **single bounded view** of the selected child (no stacking) + **separate cards** per element.
> - **Display:** the **flower** (`FlowerProgress`, larger + bloom-on-appear animation) + a **motivation line by state** (low/mid/high, from the average skill bloom, no numbers) + **skill bars** (the shared `components/bloom/SkillBars` component reused with `/studio`, **percent** format for the parent vs `x/10` for the teacher) + **next session** (informational тАФ date + teacher only, **no join button**, no lesson objective) + **latest report** + **latest result** + "View all".
> - **Locked decisions:** **no tabs** (single bounded view) ┬╖ the **plan is a one-line glimpse** in the parent account (the full plan belongs to the student account) ┬╖ the **join button belongs to the child's surface**, not the parent ┬╖ plan units count = **level** units (the `y` in "Unit x of y" is level-scoped, not whole-curriculum). *(This resolves the design parts of open item ┬з9(5) for `/guardian`: (a) language mixing ┬╖ (b) primitive flower/plan ┬╖ (d) guardianтЖФchildren structure.)*

