 with a possessive (`"╪╣┘Е╪▒ ╪з┘Д╪▓┘З╪▒╪з┘Ж┘К's flower spans 4 unitsтАж"`): a wrong concatenation pattern (no ICU), bidi-broken; likely recurs in other greetings/titles/notifications тАФ a sweep of every site injecting Arabic data into English templates is needed when opened; session notes also mix `"Strengths: <Arabic>"`. **(b) primitive components** тАФ "My flower" is a static icon with an instructional sentence, not a blooming flower; "My plan"/the guardian plan is a long unstructured text list. **(c) the four-state objective indicator** тАФ the current `ObjectivePetals` petal (teacher surface) did not satisfy visually; it is to be redesigned (four clearly-distinct states, platform identity) within this theme, not in isolation. Pinned reference: ┬з6.2 (the child sees abstract petals with no labels ┬╖ the teacher sees details on tap) тАФ the model is sound (child/guardian don't see objective assessment; details live on the teacher surface only), so the deferral is design, not logic. **(d) guardianтЖФmultiple-children structure** тАФ the account must show all of the guardian's children with smooth navigation between them (professional, matching best-in-class platforms); the current structure and presentation are weak. The architectural side (who creates the child ┬╖ the guardianтЖФchildren structure ┬╖ the navigation) is decided **first**, then the design is built on top тАФ not the reverse. **Methodology:** this theme mixes architecture (account-creation separation) + a full redesign + Claude Design involvement тАФ to be opened in a dedicated conversation that starts with a diagnostic sweep. **(6) tapтЖТdates for the objective petal** тАФ `ObjectivePetals` reveals id+label on tap; the assessment dates (┬з6.2) need expanding `lib/progress/bloom.ts` to fetch the `objective_assessments` history тАФ deliberately deferred. **(7) ~~Guardian creates a child from their own account~~ тЬЕ CLOSED (2026-06-27)** тАФ the sweep found `Add a child` to be a **dead remnant of the pre-Admin-funnel model**, so it was **deleted** (plus `grantConsent` + the consent badge/button). Registration is now exclusively Admin тЖТ `provisionAccounts`. See "тЬЕ Account-creation separation".

**Deferred (recorded 2026-06-27, for future sessions):** **(8) `/learn` (student account) redesign** тАФ not started; the full plan as a journey + a blooming flower + the unit lifecycle (this is the remaining half of item (5)). **тЪая╕П SCOPE DISCIPLINE (2026-06-28):** `/learn` and `/guardian` have known display gaps that keep surfacing incidentally (e.g. the SITE-1 session-heading still Arabic in an EN guardian account). These are **NOT** to be fixed piecemeal тАФ they belong to the `/learn` and `/guardian` **REDESIGN** sessions. **Log new such gaps here; do not open ad-hoc gates for them.** Open known gaps: (a) **guardian report heading** (`sessions.lesson_title`) not locale-aware тАФ needs `sessions.objective_id` + backfill (a future migration); (b) **orphan i18n key** `learn.plan.heading` (cleanup, after the child-plan list removal). **(9) New parent-account functions** тАФ *not started; need an architecture sweep first*. Governing principle: **the parent reads or requests, never executes** (Admin owns execution). (a) a **read-only monthly evaluation** (teacher/platform) surfaced to the parent; (b) **request forms that raise to the Admin queue** тАФ pause/cancel subscription + complaint/note. **(10) `/guardian` optional polish** тАФ a flower-card background ┬╖ a deeper avatar-switcher redesign (real child photos vs initials). **(11) Orphaned i18n key cleanup in `guardian`** тАФ `consent*` / `bloomSummary` / `sessionNotes` тАж left unused after the redesign + consent removal (connect-before-cut, prove zero readers). **(12) Plan-section (teacher) assessment UX redesign** тАФ *deferred bundle, a future dedicated session, design-first then implement. The scoring model is FROZEN/correct (see "тЬЕ Assessment model тАФ verdict 2026-06-27"); this is about the TEACHER-FACING display/UX + surfacing history, NOT the scoring math (except the L3 question):* **(a)** the 4-level objective indicators (`ObjectivePetals`) are teacher-only and visually unsatisfactory тЖТ replace with a clearer representation (numbers / percentages / other icons тАФ decide at design time). **(b)** the Seed/Bud/Balloon/Bloom rating dropdown тЖТ revisit after (a) (the input depends on how the 4 states are represented). **(c) тЬЕ CLOSED (2026-06-27):** the **dropdown-revert display bug (S1)** is fixed тАФ the rating `<select>` `defaultValue` is now unconditionally empty ("RateтАж") so it no longer mirrors the blended stage, and a read-only **"Current: {state} ┬╖ X.X/10"** indicator was added beside it (server JSX, no client component). Input and display are now separate, so a save can never look unsaved. `recordObjectiveAssessment` / `objective_assessments` / the 0056 trigger UNTOUCHED. commit `92f23f3`, Ready=HEAD, live-verified by Diya. **(d)** per-objective **assessment history** for the teacher тАФ a count + a log of each assessment (timestamp + SOURCE: teacher / auto-graded homework / unit test), since one objective is assessed several times (e.g. Reading 3├Ч = 2 homeworks + 1 unit test) тАФ the data exists (`objective_assessments` stores each with its source, ┬з10/┬з4 of the reference); only the UI is missing тАФ and it must be **editable/deletable** (remove a wrong assessment тЖТ recompute `current_value` from the remaining rows). **(e) тЬЕ RESOLVED (2026-06-27):** the **Layer-3 open question** тАФ L3 (the skill petal across started units) **stays a SIMPLE mean**, matching the frozen reference ┬з5 and the current `bloom.ts`; **NO change to code or to the frozen Curriculum Reference.** Rationale: recency is already handled at L1 (the 65/35 decaying average), so a second decaying at L3 would double-count, harm CEFR auditability, and contradict the cumulative nature of the skill тАФ and the real home for "recency matters" is the deferred temporal-wilt item. **(13) Shared-device access: family session + profile switcher + installable PWA** тАФ *large architectural item (auth/session + PWA), design-first, a dedicated session, not started.* **PROBLEM:** the platform assumes student and guardian use SEPARATE devices; on a SHARED family device, switching between the student account (join session / homework) and the guardian account forces repeated logout/login with username+password тАФ real customer friction. The fix must be **fully handled by us (automatic)**, must **NOT** ask parents to do technical steps (e.g. "save your password in the browser"), and should also remove the friction of "open a browser, then log in" (esp. mobile/tablet). **Two complementary layers:** **(a) Family session + profile switcher** (seamless switching тАФ the "Netflix 'Who's watching?'" pattern): one login establishes a **family session** that knows the guardian AND their children тЖТ a "Who's using now?" avatar screen on entry (guardian ┬╖ child1 ┬╖ child2) тЖТ a top-bar switcher to change profile later with **one tap, NO logout/login, NO re-entering credentials**. **Security guard:** the guardian profile (sensitive data) can be protected by a short **PIN** on entry while child profiles open with a single tap (Netflix/Disney+ kids-profile pattern). This is an **AUTH/SESSION architecture change** (Supabase auth + how a session carries multiple identities) тАФ not cosmetic; needs a dedicated design when opened. **(b) Installable PWA** (fast access without a browser тАФ "Add to Home Screen"): the web app becomes installable as a home-screen icon that opens full-screen like a real app, **without** a native app (no App Store, no native build). **iOS caveat 1:** Safari on iOS does NOT auto-prompt "Add to Home Screen" (unlike Chrome/Firefox) тАФ on iPhone/iPad the user adds it manually from the share menu (one step on the parent); mitigation = a simple in-app visual guide ("tap here тЖТ Add to Home Screen"). **iOS caveat 2 (stay signed in):** some iOS PWAs re-prompt login on reopen тАФ sessions must be configured so the identity **persists** after closing the app; this ties directly to layer (a) тАФ the long-lived family session is what prevents re-login. **CONSTITUTIONAL NOTE:** this does **NOT** breach the frozen "no mobile app in v1" decision тАФ a **PWA is not a mobile app** (no App Store, no native development), it is a lightweight installable web experience, fully consistent with that decision. (Documented explicitly so it is not mistaken for a v1-scope breach.) **(14) Feed AI generation inputs in English** тАФ *newly opened 2026-06-28, not actioned.* Homework / unit-test generation (`studio/actions.ts`) still reads `descriptor_ar` as the model INPUT. Switching to `descriptor_en` changes the generator **input** (a behavior change, not a display change) тАФ a separate decision to make **before** content generation. **(15) Arabic-catalog success-criteria consistency review (Ghinwa's audit notes)** тАФ *newly opened 2026-06-28, not actioned.* Three source-side weak/ambiguous criteria were flagged DURING the descriptor_en audit: (a) "in a simple way" (e.g. A1-U04-S2 / L2), (b) a listening objective whose primary act is comparison (B1-U11-L2), (c) an outcome-vague "Handles" (A2-U10-S1, source "┘К╪к╪╣╪з┘Е┘Д"). These concern the **FROZEN Arabic catalog's** criteria wording, NOT the translation тАФ open a side review **AFTER** the assessment track; **do NOT touch the frozen reference now**.

**Out of v1 scope (later):** a real payment gateway ┬╖ evaluations/requests submitted by the guardian from their account ┬╖ tracking teacher dues ┬╖ slot filtering for multiple teachers ┬╖ an in-person teaching UI for the teacher.

